09/07/2009
TIRANA, Albania -- The country is facing a threat from the swine flu virus, one that is very difficult to prevent, Alban Ylli, the head of the Public Health Institute, said on Wednesday (July 8th). 
According to him, identifying and isolating the first possible case is key. 
Ylli urged members of the public to report to hospitals if they notice any of the symptoms. 
(Shekulli, Telegrafi, News 24, Alsat - 08/07/09)
